From 2414401337b6b12b3392502285257bd1913c27b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
Date: Thu, 30 Oct 2025 16:21:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix logical replication with clusters running versions <
 6.1.0

The retention lease id used the string representation of the
shardId, which contains the `indexUUID` since v6.1.
This will break ongoing logical replication, thus reverting
back to the old string representation format for the lease id.
Additionally, shard requests from/to older nodes were resolving
their index/shardrouting by index name instead of uuid, this
adds BWC logic to fallback to resolve by-name.

Follow up of #18063.
